Test program for all implementations of JImmutableSetMap. Divided into five sections: growing (adds new key-set pairs), updating (adds and removes values in the sets of the setmap without changing the keys), shrinking (removes key-set pairs), contains (tests methods that check for keys or values in a set), and cleanup (empties the setmap of all key-set pairs).

This tester was designed so that the setmap produced would contain sets of a large variety of sizes. On average, 25% of the sets in the setmap will be empty by the end of the test. 18% will contain only one value. 52% will contain between two and ten values, and the remaining 5% will contain between eleven and over a hundred values.
